race.comment: CHAMPAGNE EXPRESS (7) was unplaced last time but that was well off best. Beaten a nose the start prior and will find this easier. Looks well placed here and can atone. PRINCE DE VEGA (6) is a three start maid but well travelled already. Solid fresh in a Super Maiden at Wagga then outclassed in richer company at Canterbury. Back in Victoria and will find this easier. Should run well. ANGELOTTI (9) is another who will find this easier. thereabouts in three runs this time in but all in richer maidens and looks tough to beat on best figures. UNRIDDLE (4) has had a lot of chances and remains a maiden. But did run well last time when placed at Moe and the start prior wasn't far away at Cranbourne in a tougher race. Has claims on best figures. MISS LIL (8) is another coming off tougher maidens and can feature on best.
